       <span style="font-weight: 400">
        <font face="Arial">
         American Sign Language:  "slow"
        </font>
       </span>
      </h2>
      <blockquote>
       <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1" width="50%"/>
       <font face="Arial">
        <p>
         <span style="font-weight: 400">
          To sign "slow," slide the dominant hand (right hand if you are right handed) up the non-dominant 
		forearm a short distance--starting at the back of the base (left) hand. 
		You only need to go a few inches.
          <br/>
          Usage note:  If you do this sign "very fast" it means "very slow."  
		If you start the sign and hold it in place for a moment, then roll your 
		eyes and then finish it quickly it means very, very slow.
         </span>
        </p>
