          In a message dated 1/4/2007 5:06:30 PM Pacific Standard Time, quiltstash@ writes:
         </div>
         <blockquote style="PADDING-LEFT: 5px; MARGIN-LEFT: 5px; BORDER-LEFT: blue 2px solid">
          <font color="#000000" face="Arial" size="2" style="BACKGROUND-COLOR: transparent">
           Is it really 
			true that if you do the sign "slow" VERY FAST it really means VERY SLOW?  That seems so backwards to me.  Can you please verify this when you get the 
			chance.
           <br/>
           Thanks,
           <br/>
